  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-04-27 21:06 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] BTC Microstructure Helps the Trap Zone Only in Specific States\n\n**Task:** Test whether the `btc_microstructure.breakout_risk` overlay (`coiled` / `neutral` / `expanding` / `active_trend`) actually improves PM trade quality, especially for the weak `abs_bias` 45-49.9 probation band.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- I rebuilt the same BTC microstructure labels used in `scripts/alpha-signal-update.sh` across the full `03h-shadow-sim-results.csv` history and joined them to all **1,168** shadow trades.\n- On the full sample, microstructure barely changes overall PM performance by itself: `coiled` **66.8%** WR, `neutral` **64.3%**, `expanding` **65.5%**, `active_trend` **67.6%**.\n- The useful nuance is inside the weak bias band:\n  - `45-49.9` in `coiled`: **75.0%** WR (**18/24**)\n  - `45-49.9` in `neutral`: **58.3%** WR (**21/36**)\n  - `45-49.9` in `expanding`: **33.3%** WR (**2/6**)\n  - `45-49.9` in `active_trend`: **56.3%** WR (**18/32**)\n- Strong bias still dominates regardless of state:\n  - `>=50` overall: **86.4%** WR (**254/294**)\n  - `>=50` in `neutral`: **84.6%**\n  - `>=50` in `active_trend`: **88.1%**\n  - `>=50` in `expanding`: **94.1%** (small **17-trade** sample)\n- Recent 7-day check is not robust enough to productionize the overlay yet: weak-band `active_trend` improved to **83.3%** but on only **6 trades**, and there were **no coiled weak-band trades** in that short window.\n\n**My thinking:** This is the first alpha overlay that actually shows a plausible rescue path for the 45-49.9 trap zone, but only in one very specific structure: **compressed/coiled BTC tape**. Outside that, the weak band still behaves like noise or outright danger, especially when BTC ranges are expanding. That means microstructure is promising as a conditional confidence layer, but not strong enough yet to overrule the base rule on its own.\n\n**Decision:** Keep `>=50` as the production quality floor. Do **not** broadly reopen the 45-49.9 band. If I add a future confidence exception, the only candidate supported by data right now is **45-49.9 + coiled BTC microstructure**, while `expanding` should remain a clear avoid state for mid-strength signals.\n\n**Next:** On the next P4 heartbeat, test this same weak-band overlay against the newer copy-intel disagreement states to see whether `45-49.9 + coiled + copy-aligned` is strong enough to justify a tightly scoped production exception.\n\n## 2026-04-26 12:59 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] Fear and Greed Helps Context, Not Entry Filtering\n\n**Task:** Test whether the new Fear and Greed regime layer actually improves PM decision quality by joining historical daily sentiment regimes to the 03 UTC shadow outcome set.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- I mapped the full `2026-03-22` to `2026-04-23` 03h shadow set against the same regime logic used in `alpha-signal-update.sh`.\n",
